cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Literature-review pipeline (citation-graph-driven literature survey)"
message: >-
  If you use this software in your research, please cite it and acknowledge
  the author. (The MIT license already requires keeping the copyright notice;
  this is the academic-acknowledgment request on top of that.)
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Schwenkler
    given-names: John
abstract: >-
  A reusable, topic-agnostic workflow for building a citation-graph-driven
  literature review in a focused subliterature, then sorting it by issue into a
  reading order. Standalone Python scripts that call a large language model
  (Claude by default, provider-swappable) for relevance, issue-discovery, and
  depth-of-engagement scoring.
keywords:
  - literature-review
  - citation-graph
  - bibliometrics
  - large-language-models
  - research-tools
license: MIT
version: 0.1.0-beta
date-released: 2026-06-05
